The paper deals with the problem of finding the largest subset of points in general position, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The paper also presents an algorithm and experimental evaluation, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories.
